	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK14_Precedents_p-text">
    <title>p/text <lnpid>id-UK14-30220</lnpid></title>
    <body>
        <section><p><sourcexml>p/text</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>p/text</targetxml> as described
                in General Markup section.</p>
            <p><b>EXCEPT:</b> When target parent is <targetxml>form:bodytext</targetxml>,
                    <sourcexml>p/text</sourcexml> becomes
                <targetxml>form:p/form:text</targetxml></p></section>
        <section><p><b><u>Special handling for cover-date
                    paragraphs:</u></b></p><p><sourcexml>p[@class="cover-date"]</sourcexml> becomes
                    <targetxml>form:clause[@clausetype="cover-date"]/form:bodytext/form:p</targetxml></p><p>The
                rosetta cover-date paragraph occurs only within <sourcexml>frm:div</sourcexml> so
                target wrapper <targetxml>form:clause</targetxml> allowed. See Example 2
            below.</p></section>

        <pre>
        <b>EXAMPLE 1: Target parent is <targetxml>form:bodytext</targetxml></b>
            
<b><i>Source XML</i></b>

&lt;clause id="ukContentItemdbc1fd8e-da3c-4507-ac1e-988dca3ab37f"&gt;
  &lt;heading&gt;
    &lt;desig&gt;
      &lt;designum&gt;1&lt;/designum&gt;
    &lt;/desig&gt;
  &lt;/heading&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;text&gt;The reversioner admits...&lt;/text&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/clause&gt;
 
<b><i>Target XML</i></b>

&lt;form:clause&gt;
  &lt;ref:anchor id="ukContentItemdbc1fd8e-da3c-4507-ac1e-988dca3ab37f" anchortype="local"/&gt;
  &lt;heading&gt;
    &lt;desig&gt;1&lt;/desig&gt;
  &lt;/heading&gt;
  &lt;form:bodytext&gt;
    &lt;form:p&gt;
      &lt;form:text&gt;The reversioner admits...&lt;/form:text&gt;
    &lt;/form:p&gt;
  &lt;/form:bodytext&gt;
&lt;/form:clause&gt;

                </pre>
        <pre>
        <b>EXAMPLE 2: cover-date paragraph</b>
            
<b><i>Source XML</i></b>

&lt;frm:div divtype="cover"&gt;
    &lt;heading&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;Loan note instrument: share purchase&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;/heading&gt;
    &lt;p class="cover-date"&gt;
        &lt;text&gt;
            &lt;frm:prompt&gt;Dated __________ 20__&lt;/frm:prompt&gt;
        &lt;/text&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
        &lt;text&gt;
            &lt;emph typestyle="bf"&gt;LOAN NOTE INSTRUMENT&lt;/emph&gt;
        &lt;/text&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/frm:div&gt;
 
<b><i>Target XML</i></b>

&lt;form:div divtype="cover"&gt;
    &lt;heading&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;Loan note instrument: share purchase&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;/heading&gt;
    &lt;form:bodytext&gt;
        &lt;form:clause clausetype="cover-date"&gt;
            &lt;form:bodytext&gt;
                &lt;form:p&gt;
                    &lt;form:text&gt;
                        &lt;form:prompt&gt;Dated __________ 20__&lt;/form:prompt&gt;
                    &lt;/form:text&gt;
                &lt;/form:p&gt;
            &lt;/form:bodytext&gt;
        &lt;/form:clause&gt;
        &lt;form:p&gt;
            &lt;form:text&gt;
                &lt;emph typestyle="bf"&gt;LOAN NOTE INSTRUMENT&lt;/emph&gt;
            &lt;/form:text&gt;
        &lt;/form:p&gt;
    &lt;/form:bodytext&gt;
&lt;/form:div&gt;

                </pre>
        <section>
            <title>Changes</title>
            <p>2013-11-11: <ph id="change_20131111_jm">Illustrative. Ancillary to this section.
                    Corrected example to show <sourcexml>clause[@id]</sourcexml> mapped to
                        <targetxml>ref:anchor[@id]</targetxml>.</ph></p>
            <p>2013-10-30: <ph id="change_20131030_jm">Added special rule for
                        <sourcexml>p[@class="cover-date"]</sourcexml>. The attribute is new in Oct
                    2013 redelivery. A <targetxml>form:clause</targetxml> wrapper will be generated
                    but this is not a new target xpath. Webteam 239323.</ph></p>
        </section>
